Environment Variables

# 

<span key="7e3fc2cc257e409baf8a43efe939ceb6"><span offset-key="7e3fc2cc257e409baf8a43efe939ceb6:0">Environment Variables</span></span>

<span key="a54fcf3d2be54c79814b525f2489919f"><span offset-key="a54fcf3d2be54c79814b525f2489919f:0">Environment variables are used to configure your application to run in a specific environment. These environments are generally local development (your laptop), production (a hosted server), and other hosted servers related to non-production environments.</span></span>

<span key="6e16c74f846344cc8a1fe5f04bfa0465"><span offset-key="6e16c74f846344cc8a1fe5f04bfa0465:0">There should be a single set of environment variables for your application, with each environment simply defining different values for those variables.</span></span>

<span key="f73b99743e794b91bf73410e5fb9125d"><span offset-key="f73b99743e794b91bf73410e5fb9125d:0">https://www.lucidchart.com/publicSegments/view/9df797cf-e1fb-4ff4-9d82-b2136344f405/image.png</span></span>

<span key="8f88baa52848410facbba9948bfa80ea"><span offset-key="8f88baa52848410facbba9948bfa80ea:0">One set of environment variables, different values for each environment.</span></span>

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

<span key="b7b68167ef41453b852c0835160085ac"><span offset-key="b7b68167ef41453b852c0835160085ac:0">You'll need to set up your environment variables in order to run your applications and develop locally.</span></span>

<span key="5371f4f13770463faa586d5e369484e0"><span offset-key="5371f4f13770463faa586d5e369484e0:0">For more information about security and protecting your secrets, </span></span><a href="https://docs.labs.lambdaschool.com/home/#please-read-this-carefully" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="cb434a04f24f434aa7e262077e133c1b" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-5045_259-5046-237__"><span data-key="1bae98e384db48cba3047a02e9c85f8f"><span data-offset-key="1bae98e384db48cba3047a02e9c85f8f:0">please see our entry in the Labs Guides.</span></span></span></a><span key="7e56ffb1925a41159b6e0109d9117dd0"><span offset-key="7e56ffb1925a41159b6e0109d9117dd0:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

## 

<span key="4f4af37e03fa4d7f96167a129ce14d2f"><span offset-key="4f4af37e03fa4d7f96167a129ce14d2f:0">Things not to do</span></span>

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

<span key="be0fda3add5849999e09dd56e395efbf">**Checking in files like your .env or secrets file to git and GitHub is a major security flaw**<span offset-key="be0fda3add5849999e09dd56e395efbf:1">, and there are some secrets and keys you'll use in Labs that will be flagged automatically by bots scanning for such incidents. If you check in secrets to version control during Labs, expect to have to work with your engineering manager to scrub them from your git history!</span></span>

## 

<span key="66d56f79e3484f06b51c26259b57d37d"><span offset-key="66d56f79e3484f06b51c26259b57d37d:0">Anti-pattern #1</span></span>

<span key="1db1cde5cc92408eb7926fffb247a9c5"><span offset-key="1db1cde5cc92408eb7926fffb247a9c5:0">Having your application try to figure out which environment variables to use depending on the value of another environment variable.</span></span>

1

<span key="1efa4b8225e64cb1a8119513ee02b84a"><span offset-key="1efa4b8225e64cb1a8119513ee02b84a:0">import axios from "axios";</span></span>

2

<span key="2475fb065e0c403488db4a48bce5376c"><span offset-key="2475fb065e0c403488db4a48bce5376c:0"><span slate-zero-width="n">â€‹</span></span></span>

3

<span key="b72ae1763b104568a96f2504a9a2f5b6"><span offset-key="b72ae1763b104568a96f2504a9a2f5b6:0">axios.defaults.baseURL = (function() {</span></span>

4

<span key="9fcb777ea5dc4d4ea453cbd43e30a0e2"><span offset-key="9fcb777ea5dc4d4ea453cbd43e30a0e2:0"> switch (process.env.REACT\_APP\_ENV) {</span></span>

5

<span key="99cf673db9664ec4bea5465886532823"><span offset-key="99cf673db9664ec4bea5465886532823:0"> case "development":</span></span>

6

<span key="78000cc1125241969c7d8a6da9812237"><span offset-key="78000cc1125241969c7d8a6da9812237:0"> return process.env.REACT\_APP\_LOCAL\_HOST;</span></span>

7

<span key="7563d0b2d7f94a3ea749d08ff8f3ff04"><span offset-key="7563d0b2d7f94a3ea749d08ff8f3ff04:0"> case "staging":</span></span>

8

<span key="0e9de2daacae4fd88504d7d8696ee369"><span offset-key="0e9de2daacae4fd88504d7d8696ee369:0"> return process.env.REACT\_APP\_STAGING\_URL;</span></span>

9

<span key="35e9bb8426124feb8fb027914c5dc0d2"><span offset-key="35e9bb8426124feb8fb027914c5dc0d2:0"> case "production":</span></span>

10

<span key="70ae153adfde4a2aaf37d65649621be7"><span offset-key="70ae153adfde4a2aaf37d65649621be7:0"> return process.env.REACT\_APP\_PRODUCTION\_URL;</span></span>

11

<span key="5af03d2d75c6460698d7b7e77b7c2c90"><span offset-key="5af03d2d75c6460698d7b7e77b7c2c90:0"> default:</span></span>

12

<span key="265d5d157c824641b47bd62536bb7fc8"><span offset-key="265d5d157c824641b47bd62536bb7fc8:0"> return process.env.REACT\_APP\_LOCAL\_HOST;</span></span>

13

<span key="b4eb2886418249249a25d958807b4f77"><span offset-key="b4eb2886418249249a25d958807b4f77:0"> }</span></span>

14

<span key="9af622d5a3794d778e7bbd7b7153bc12"><span offset-key="9af622d5a3794d778e7bbd7b7153bc12:0">})();</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-h7gdob r-10ptun7" />

Copied!

<span key="1cabd7de8a3f440a9ccf1b25f7aa00e1"><span offset-key="1cabd7de8a3f440a9ccf1b25f7aa00e1:0">There should only be one variable for the base URL, something like REACT\_APP\_AXIOS\_BASE\_URL. The value of this environment variable will be set to a value that depends on the environment where the app is running.</span></span>

<span key="dc1390c1089045b4b98864b5b9d7e405"><span offset-key="dc1390c1089045b4b98864b5b9d7e405:0">The environment variable REACT\_APP\_ENV probably shouldn't exist, as in general, the app doesn't need to know what environment it's running in, it just needs to know the values of the variables it requires to run.</span></span>

<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1vzi8xi" />

<span key="127581b4c6094e6a8fa848b6ba2c4abd"><span offset-key="127581b4c6094e6a8fa848b6ba2c4abd:0">Why? Because this makes your application confusing to deploy and manage. Having an extra layer of environment settings doubles the chances that something will go wrong. Keep it simple!</span></span>

<span key="74e0ca899a5c4f0aa001dfdf46de3634"><span offset-key="74e0ca899a5c4f0aa001dfdf46de3634:0">Plus, you almost never want your application to behave differently depending on which environment it's in. If it does, how will you be sure that it'll behave properly in production?</span></span>
